title: For Sale:  NOVESKE N4 ROGUE HUNTER 5.56 NATO 16” SS BARREL BLACK - PMAGS INCLUDED
postcontent:
NOVESKE N4 ROGUE HUNTER 5.56 NATO 16” SS BARREL BLACK

Noveske stainless barrels are made to fill a precision role while retaining flawless function. Retaining accuracy and reliability is a complicated balance in that the chamber needs to be slightly modified from the NATO to improve bullet hook-up in the throat, while keeping to functional properties of the NATO body dimensions. The result is Noveske proprietary chambering. The steel used is a type of 416r and hardened to about 30 HRC prior to any machining. These barrels are button rifled with Noveske proprietary 7 PT button. This rifling profile differs from that in the chrome lined barrel line in that the lands have a slightly more trapezoidal shape. This design and the type of stainless used helps the lead edge of the rifling from eroding as fast as it might with conventional rifling, and the barrels tend to outlast others.



For use in any precision application, we recommend the stainless barrel for its edge in accuracy and excellent reliability.

title: For Sale:  Ithaca Model 37 12ga Riot Gun (WWII - 1943 vintage)
postcontent:
This is NOT a factory Riot Gun. It was cut down from a longer barreled gun. The barrel is 20-inches and is now a CYL bore.

This gun was indeed born in 1943 (SN 647xx). The important things to look for on old Ithacas like this... the serial number on the barrel and receiver match. There is no pitting in the barrel. Only the slightest crack in the stock at the wrist (its not all busted up), the butt end of the stock is also well intact. The gun has been around for 71-years and has been used, both the wood and the metal show wear. The gun functions flawlessly (slam fires – if that's your thing) and is just a neat old gun. It would make a wonderful and inexpensive addition to someone's WWII collection.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Springfield Savage Stevens Model 187S, 22 Semi-Auto Rifle
location: Fort Thomas, KY near Cincinnati, Northern Kentucky, Kentucky
postcontent: A very nice, classic Springfield Model 187S, made by Savage Stevens Springfield.  About a 14 round tube magazine, barrel length is 20".  One of an older series often called a "gill gun" for the cut-outs on the left side of the receiver.  These guns have a distinctive action, they tell me is not unlike an AR, where the bolt doesn't close until the trigger is released.  It's interesting and neat.  I really like the gun and enjoy shooting it.  Truth be told, I am selling off  several 22 rifles because my old eyes don't function well with irons sights (trust me, it will happen to you soon enough).  I could add an aperture sight but that would mean drilling and tapping a classic and I won't do that.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Stevens Model 87C
location: Fort Thomas, KY near Cincinnati, Northern Kentucky, Kentucky
postcontent: Stevens 87C, 22 LR.  16+ tube mag, about a 22" barrel.  Very nice older rifle made by Savage Stevens Springfield  One of an older series often called a "gill gun" for the cut-outs on the left side of the receiver.  These guns have a distinctive action, they tell me is not unlike an AR, where the bolt doesn't close until the trigger is released.  It's interesting and neat.  I really like the gun and enjoy shooting it.  Truth be told, I am selling off  several 22 rifles because my old eyes don't function well with iron sights (trust me, it will happen to you soon enough).  I could add an aperture sight but that would mean drilling and tapping a classic and I won't do that.
